Program: Omnibus
Title: Palace of Variety
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0376kkc
Last Broadcast Date: 02 April 1993
A look at the art of parliamentary oratory in the British Houses of Parliament with examples of good debating styles from Michael Foot, Margaret Thatcher in her final speech before leaving Parliament and Harold Macmillan in his maiden speech in the House of Lords at the age of 90.